HEADWORD: Coltsfoot
<hw>Colts"foot`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A perennial herb (<spn>Tussilago Farfara</spn>), whose leaves and
rootstock are sometimes employed in medicine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Butterbur coltsfoot</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a
